title: The Three Stigmata of Palmer Eldritch
notes: As crazy as ever, and often tricky to follow the flips in and out of realities, but ultimately very inventive and enjoyable book.

title: The Long Race to Glory: How the British Came to Rule the Cycling World
notes: Not much more than a timeline through British Cycling history, namechecking loads of people along the way. Not a huge amount of analysis.

title: Moranthology
notes: Fun. In digestible chunks. I liked the more serious writing more than the amusing throwaway stuff, but that was good too.
